  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Compound-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is documented at the COU level; however, the bound claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance link (W-EP-01, Critical) and the primary validation result omits a hasUncertaintyQuantification entry (W-AL-01, High). Both weakeners coexist on this UnitOfAssurance, triggering COMPOUND-01. Decision recorded as Accepted to mask the compound deficiency.",
