    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Credibility factors assessed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 categories. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification conducted at the COU level provides confidence in hemolysis predictions. Achieved levels are below required levels for several factors, but the assessment team judges the overall evidence package sufficient for regulatory submission given the conservative nature of the power-law hemolysis model. All validation comparisons pass the 15% NIH tolerance criterion.",
